[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dukinfield girl, 15, in hospital after taking unknown drug

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 15-year-old girl has been taken to hospital after taking an unknown drug, believed to be a type of amphetamine.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police said they received a report that the girl, from Dukinfield, Tameside, Greater Manchester, had been admitted to hospital at about 22:50 BST on Friday.
She is believed to have suffered a bad reaction after possibly taking a drug known as Magic, police said.
She remains in hospital where her condition is described as stable.
